---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Columns from '../components/Columns.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
import SplitList from '../components/SplitList.astro';
import LargeText from '../components/typography/LargeText.astro';
import LeadText from '../components/typography/LeadText.astro';
import NormalText from '../components/typography/NormalText.astro';
import portrait from '../images/portrait.jpg';

const howColumns = [
  {
    title: 'UX & Product Design',
    text: 'I make complex software feel effortless. No clutter, no confusing menus. Just digital products built around how people actually think, from the first sketch to the final pixel.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Cyber Security & Resilience',
    text: 'To build a secure system, you have to know how to break it. I look for the hidden breaking points in software, protocols, and human habits to fix tech vulnerabilities before they become real-world problems.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Radio & Communication Tech',
    text: 'I tinker with frequencies, electronics, and off-grid communication. Building independent radio networks is my way of understanding how digital infrastructure works when you strip away the safety net of the mainstream internet.',
  },
];

const pathItems = [
  {
    label: 'Digital Communication',
    value:
      'My roots are in digital communication, where I realized early on just how powerfully technology shapes human attention, behavior, and—most importantly—trust.',
  },
  {
    label: 'Project Leadership',
    value:
      'Managing complex projects showed me what happens when noble strategies meet real-world chaos. I learned how to bridge the gap between technical constraints, messy organizational realities, and actual human needs.',
  },
  {
    label: 'Product & Experience Design',
    value:
      "Today, my focus is on making complex systems digestible. I design interfaces, workflows, and digital products that don't overwhelm users, turning confusing software into tools that feel natural to use.",
  },
  {
    label: 'Independent Systems & Community',
    value:
      "In my free time, I build independent software, experiment with ham radio, and advocate for security. It's my way of exploring how we can stay connected, resilient, and self-reliant, completely independent of big tech and centralized platforms.",
  },
];
const focusItems = [
  {
    title: 'Complex Interfaces',
    text: "Heavy-duty products and systems where users can't afford to guess. I step in when people need absolute clarity, navigation, and confidence to get the job done, instead of fighting clunky UX.",
  },
  {
    title: 'Responsible Digital Products',
    text: 'Tech that actually respects the user. This means embedding privacy, digital autonomy, and transparency directly into the design—especially when handling sensitive workflows where ethical decisions matter just as much as the code.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Systems & Communication',
    text: 'Projects under the hood. I love working on resilient infrastructure, off-grid communication tech, independent networks, and environments where the underlying technology is genuinely demanding.',
  },
];
const rulesOnAI = [
  {
    title: 'Keep human skills alive',
    text: 'AI should be a bicycle for the mind, not a self-driving car. It should augment our thinking and creativity, never replace our fundamental ability to operate and solve problems without a machine.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Efficiency is not resilience',
    text: "When you optimize a system solely for speed, scale, and cost, you build something incredibly fragile. We shouldn't create a world that depends entirely on infrastructure that only a handful of people still understand.",
  },
  {
    title: 'Tech reshapes responsibility',
    text: 'Tools are never neutral. Every new technology rewires how we communicate, work, and depend on one another. We need to weigh these human consequences before we push automation to a point of no return.',
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout title='Designing technology for humans - Ralph Bolliger'>
  <Section id='why' margin='base'>
    <div slot='left'>
      <NormalText spaceAfter='small' weight='bold' tone='accent'>Why</NormalText
      >
    </div>
    <div slot='right'>
      <LeadText weight='normal' spaceAfter='large'>
        Technology should back us up, not dictate how we live. I build digital
        systems that don't restrict human freedom, but actually unlock it,
        giving people real autonomy in a hyper-connected world.
      </LeadText>
      <LeadText weight='normal'>
        Systems get more complex every day, and we can't change that. But we can
        stop that complexity from turning into chaos. To me, true resilience
        goes way beyond mere efficiency. It's about keeping organizations
        capable of acting even when things go sideways.</LeadText
      >
    </div>
  </Section>
  <Section id='how' border='none'>
    <div slot='left'>
      <NormalText spaceAfter='small' weight='bold' tone='accent'>How</NormalText
      >
    </div>
    <div slot='right'>
      <Columns columns={howColumns} />
      <LargeText class='mt-base-double'>
        Privacy isn't about hiding; it's about staying in control.
      </LargeText>
    </div>
  </Section>
  <Section id='practice'>
    <div slot='left'>
      <NormalText spaceAfter='small' weight='bold' tone='accent'
        >Practice</NormalText
      >
    </div>
    <div slot='right'>
      <LargeText spaceAfter='large'
        >My career started in digital communication, shifted into project
        leadership, and eventually led me deep into product and experience
        design. When I'm not working with clients, I'm usually down a rabbit
        hole. Whether that's ethical hacking, philosophy, behavioral psychology,
        or tinkering with amateur radio.</LargeText
      >
      <LargeText spaceAfter='large'
        >To me, these aren't random, isolated hobbies; they are different lenses
        for looking at the exact same thing: how humans interact with technology
        and infrastructure.</LargeText
      >
      <NormalText weight='bold' class='mt-base-double mb-base-double'
        >Path</NormalText
      >
      <SplitList items={pathItems} />
      <LargeText class='mt-base'
        >Complexity is a given. Confusion shouldn't be.</LargeText
      >
    </div>
  </Section>
  <Section id='focus'>
    <div slot='left'>
      <NormalText spaceAfter='small' weight='bold' tone='accent'
        >Focus</NormalText
      >
    </div>
    <div slot='right'>
      <LargeText class='mb-base-double'
        >I'm at my best when a project sits at the crossroads of design, deep
        tech, and real-world responsibility. I get excited about complicated
        systems that need to be made simple, and situations where winning a
        user's trust depends entirely on how information is handled and
        communicated.</LargeText
      >
      <Columns columns={focusItems} />
    </div>
  </Section>
  <Section id='ai'>
    <div slot='left'>
      <NormalText spaceAfter='small' weight='bold' tone='accent'
        >AI & Human Capability</NormalText
      >
    </div>
    <div slot='right'>
      <LargeText class='mb-base-double'
        >I use AI when it genuinely helps to smooth out workflows, spark ideas,
        or improve accessibility. But I am deeply skeptical of handing over
        human understanding to permanent automation. Efficiency is not the same
        as resilience.</LargeText
      >
      <LargeText class='mb-base-double'
        >If a society outsources too much of its thinking and core expertise to
        black-box systems, we risk losing our cognitive muscle memory. We need
        to keep the skills required to look under the hood and fix things
        ourselves when those systems inevitably fail, go offline, or become too
        expensive to maintain.</LargeText
      >
      <NormalText weight='bold' class='mt-base-double mb-base-double'
        >My principles for AI</NormalText
      >
      <Columns columns={rulesOnAI} />
      <LargeText class='mt-base-double'
        >Technology should sharpen human competence, not make it obsolete.</LargeText
      >
    </div>
  </Section>
  <Section id='identity'>
    <div slot='left'>
      <NormalText spaceAfter='small' weight='bold' tone='accent'
        >Identity</NormalText
      >
    </div>
    <div slot='right'>
      <Image
        alt='Portrait of myself'
        src={portrait}
        data-reveal
        class='mb-base-double rounded-2xl shadow-2xl'
      />
      <LargeText class='mb-base-double'
        >I don't publish direct contact info out in the open. If you need to
        verify who I am or want to set up a secure, encrypted line of
        communication, you can use my public OpenPGP key:</LargeText
      >
      <NormalText>
        <a
          title='Click to get OpenPGP key'
          href='/pgp'
          class='font-mono text-accent underline underline-offset-4'
          rel='noreferrer'
          target='_blank'
        >
          FC84 CC79 8DD1 C935 6857<br />6F3B EE36 9AC6 9EF1 7BD8
        </a>
      </NormalText>
      <LargeText class='mt-base-double'
        >As digital systems demand more of our trust, knowing exactly who you
        are dealing with is a necessity, not an afterthought.</LargeText
      >
    </div>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>
